Comment_glosser: Here the form for 6 is different from number 6 that is ɖu
In this language there are different ligartures have been used for the fomration of complex numerals. They are sɑ, zɑ, ɲɑ̃, rɑ, don, ɡjɑ and ɡo
Ligatures are not used in higher multiplicative numerals.
The order of the constituents of the ‘Thousands’ vary from ‘Hundreds’; as in Hundreds ‘atoms precedes the base’, and it is vice versa in thousands, that is ‘base precedes the atom’.
